																								 New Delhi, Nov. 5: Direct tax collections maintained a growth of over 40 per cent in the April-October period. The collections are set to surpass revenues from indirect taxes for the first time. The direct tax collection went up by 43.15 per cent for the period ended October 31 to Rs 1,28,864 crore from Rs 90,180 crore during the same period last fiscal. Corporate tax recorded a growth of 45.71 per cent at Rs 78,785 crore, compared with Rs 54,072 crore in the previous fiscal.																								 London/Mumbai, Nov. 5: The Tata group is considering a listing on the London bourses for a new entity. The group will finally make its London stock market debut through a participation in a hush-hush new venture called the Mango Tree India fund, a report in the Sunday Times said. However, the groups headquarters in India dismissed any such move. 																								 New Delhi, Nov. 5: Ministers from G-20 countries, including India and Brazil, will meet in Geneva on November 15 to renew efforts toward closing the gap in the Doha round of wto negotiations.																								 Shanghai, Nov. 5: PetroChina shares more than doubled in its market debut after it raised $9 billion in the worlds biggest IPO this year. The oil producer became the worlds biggest listed company by market value at around $1 trillion.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 5: Pidilite Industries will acquire the plant and machinery of an international speciality chemical company for Rs 450 crore.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 5: Public sector banks must upgrade technology to provide services to people who have not been tapped so far, finance minister P. Chidambaram said today while inaugurating the Union Bank of Indias technology centre.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 5: The private sector is expected to pump in Rs 4,00,000 crore into Indias infrastructure in the next five years, global consultancy firm Ernst amp; Young said. 
